      "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\">Dr. Sharma, a district health officer, is attending a national workshop on disaster management strategies. During one of the discussions, a fellow delegate mentions the pivotal role of the National Disaster Management Authority (NDMA) in coordinating response mechanisms. Dr. Sharma, being new to the field, is curious about the leadership hierarchy of NDMA. Who is at the helm of the National Disaster Management Authority (NDMA)?</span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q6075851",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 34732,
      "difficulty_level": "beginner",
      "subjects_id": [
        7
      ],
      "solution": "<p><span style=\"color:black;font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Ans. B. Prime Minister</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Explanation:</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">The <strong>National Disaster Management Authority</strong> is located in&nbsp;<strong>New Delhi</strong>. It was formed in the year <strong>2005</strong> under the <strong>Ministry of Home Affairs</strong>. NDMA is <strong>headed </strong>by <strong>Prime Minister</strong>.&nbsp;NDMA is under the&nbsp;<strong>Ministry of Home Affairs.&nbsp;</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><img src=\"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQyX3YDhn9dy-uNhsaSqqyAgUiykXgfo8YIjoR95LRU4w&amp;s\" alt=\"National Disaster Management Authority (India) - Wikipedia\"></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:black;font-size:12pt;\">At the <strong>district level</strong>, the <strong>District Collector </strong>is the <strong>chief executive</strong> of the <strong>disaster management cell.</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:black;font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Medical response&nbsp;</strong>would be <strong>headed</strong> by the <strong>Chief medical officer</strong> of the <strong>district.</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:black;font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Educational Objective:</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:black;font-size:12pt;\"><strong>National Disaster Management Authority&nbsp;</strong>(NDMA) - <strong>Headed</strong> by the <strong>Prime Minister of India</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"color:black;font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Reference: Textbook of Community Medicine by Rajvir Balwar, 1<sup>st</sup> ed, Pg 717</strong></span></p>",
